# Documentation and handoffs

## Naming

- **Anchor docs** (canonical, no date prefix): `domain-model.md`, `solution-proposal.md`
- **Design / plan docs:** `{date}-{name}-design.md` (e.g. `2026-06-01-ingestion-pipeline-design.md`)
- **Final PDFs:** `lbkmk-{name}-v{major}.{minor}.pdf`
- **Review HTML:** no version in filename (e.g. `lbkmk-resilience-strategy.html`)
- On revision: bump version in **filename and document body** (major.minor only)

## Handoff bridges (`docs/.handoff/`)

- Dated handoffs are **gitignored**; write to the **primary checkout’s** `docs/.handoff/` so the next session finds them after a worktree is removed.
- Only `docs/.handoff/README.md` is committed.
- After meaningful work (merged PR, mid-flight branch, decisions not in plan/PR/memory), write `docs/.handoff/YYYY-MM-DD-<branch-or-topic-slug>.md` — **do not commit** it.
- If losing the worktree erases context the next session needs → **handoff**, not only `docs/.context/<feature>/`.

See **`docs/.handoff/README.md`** for when to write and the document skeleton.

## Per-feature process artifacts

- `docs/.context/{feature}/` is gitignored transient material (checkpoints, review feedback). Distinct from handoffs.

## Project status

- `docs/project-status.yaml` is the machine-readable delivery record; hand-edit at phase start, stage/PR changes, and merge (see `CLAUDE.md` and `docs/plans/2026-06-02-project-status-yaml-design.md`).

## Doc build

```bash
scripts/build-docs.sh   # domain-model + solution-proposal → docs/dist/
```
